<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-426-428  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 426 428.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  July 10 1989 v217 n2 p11(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Videotex industry renews optimism. (Videotex Industry Associationconference)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mason, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Videotex Industry Association's annual conference in SanFrancisco focused on building a mass market for videotex services.andO;The unusually upbeat mood of the conference was due to the U.S.andO;District Court's decision to allow Bell regional holding companies(RHC) to provide information gateways.andP;  Southwestern BellTelephone's audio and videotex test in Houston is exceedingexpectations, with call volume going up faster than customer basegrowth.andP;  The test is the only one being conducted for the massmarket in the US and many believe that the health of the videotexbusiness relies heavily the success of the trials.andP;  A majorargument among industry insiders revolves around whether to relyon PC users as a customer base or to have RHC's distributeterminals.andP;  Other topics discussed at the conference includedcontent regulations, use of fiber optics and industrystandardization.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Videotex Industry AssociationVideotexConferencesMarketing StrategyGovernment RegulationBell Regional Holding CompaniesGateways (Interface).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>